TY  - JOUR
T1  - Development of a Tool for Measuring and Analyzing Computer User Satisfaction
AU  - Bailey, James E.
AU  - Pearson, Sammy W.
Y1  - 1983/05/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.5.530
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.29.5.530
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 530
EP  - 545
VL  - 29
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper reports on a technique for measuring and analyzing computer user satisfaction. Starting with the literature and using the critical incident interview technique, 39 factors affecting satisfaction were identified. Adapting the semantic differential scaling technique, a questionnaire for measuring satisfaction was then created. Finally, the instrument was pilot tested to prove its validity and reliability. The results of this effort and suggested uses of the questionnaire are reported here.
AB  - This paper reports on a technique for measuring and analyzing computer user satisfaction. Starting with the literature and using the critical incident interview technique, 39 factors affecting satisfaction were identified. Adapting the semantic differential scaling technique, a questionnaire for measuring satisfaction was then created. Finally, the instrument was pilot tested to prove its validity and reliability. The results of this effort and suggested uses of the questionnaire are reported here.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.5.530
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.29.5.530
Y2  - 2024/03/28
