TY  - JOUR
T1  - Market Value Maximization and Markov Dynamic Programming
AU  - Grinold, Richard C.
Y1  - 1983/05/01
PY  - 1983
DA  - 1983/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.5.583
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.29.5.583
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 583
EP  - 594
VL  - 29
IS  - 5
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper shows how an operational method for solving dynamic programs can be used, in some cases, to solve the problem of maximizing a firm's market value. The problem is formulated as a Markov decision problem that can be solved via linear programming. The paper shows how to calculate (or estimate) the state-contingent prices that are used to value the firm. In addition, the paper points out how states can be aggregated to make the solution technique more practical. The paper's final section contains a specific example.
AB  - This paper shows how an operational method for solving dynamic programs can be used, in some cases, to solve the problem of maximizing a firm's market value. The problem is formulated as a Markov decision problem that can be solved via linear programming. The paper shows how to calculate (or estimate) the state-contingent prices that are used to value the firm. In addition, the paper points out how states can be aggregated to make the solution technique more practical. The paper's final section contains a specific example.
SN  - 0025-1909
M3  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.29.5.583
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1287/mnsc.29.5.583
Y2  - 2024/03/28
